This `Stack` class is using a Python list to store the elements of the stack. Elements are removed and added to the end of the list, following a Last In, First Out (LIFO) order. The class provides several methods for stack operations, such as `push` to add an element to the top of the stack, `pop` to remove the top-most element, `peek` to view the top-most element without removing it, and `size` to check the number of elements in the stack.

